conducts fundamental macro research and securities analysis. Prior to working for Guild Investment Management, Mr. von Abele most recently worked in global regulatory affairs for several pharmaceutical and biotechnology firms. Mr. von Abele co-authors and edits Guild’s Market Commentary.Tim ShirataExecutive Vice PresidentMr. Shirata graduated from California State University, Fullerton in 2005 with a B.A. in Business Administration and a dual concentration in Marketing and Finance. Mr. Shirata is active in operations, client services, and marketing. Mr. Shirata is an active member of the Los Angeles Financial Planning Association, and has served on its  board of directors.Aubrey FordDirector of Client RelationsAubrey Ford joined Guild in 2008. Mr. Ford is the Director of Client Relations and can assist clients and prospective clients with their questions about Guild Investment Management’s portfolio management services and solutions.Barbara ReamsAdministrative ProfessionalBarbara Reams joined Guild in 2006.  Ms. Reams is an administrative professional and is available to assist with client inquiries, information changes, and administrative functions, and will see that concerns and issues are directed to the appropriate team member.Bronwyn von AbeleMarketing AssociateBronwyn von Abele joined Guild in 2010.  Ms. von Abele is an administrative professional and is available to assist with client inquiries, information changes, and administrative functions, and will see that concerns and issues are directed to the appropriate team member.  Ms. von Abele holds a B.A. in Liberal Arts.Guild Investment Management Fully discretionary investment portfolio management  LEARN MORE     


